auto.description: Default value depending on series type.

centeredSegmented.description: Data points will be connected with a centered segmented line.

centeredStepped.description: Data points will be connected with a centered stepped line.

curved.description: Data points will be connected with a curved line.

none.description: Data points will not be connected.

segmented.description: Data points will be connected with a segmented line.

stepped.description: Data points will be connected with a stepped line.

straight.description: Data points will be connected with a straight line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

off.description: Data markers belonging to the series will not be displayed.

on.description: Data markers belonging to the series will be displayed.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data marker shape will be based on chart type.

circle.description: Data markers will be circular in shape.

diamond.description: Data markers will be diamond in shape.

human.description: Data markers will be human in shape.

plus.description: Data markers will be plus in shape.

square.description: Data markers will be square in shape.

star.description: Data markers will be star in shape.

triangleDown.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing down.

triangleUp.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing up.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the series, displayed in the legend and tooltips.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the series. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

auto.description: No pattern is applied to data item fill.

largeChecker.description: Large checker pattern is applied to the data item.

largeCrosshatch.description: Large cross hatch pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiagonalLeft.description: Large diagonal left pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiagonalRight.description: Large diagonal right pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiamond.description: Large diamond pattern is applied to the data item.

largeTriangle.description: Large triangle pattern is applied to the data item.

smallChecker.description: Small checker pattern is applied to the data item.

smallCrosshatch.description: Small cross hatch pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiagonalLeft.description: Small diagonal left pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiagonalRight.description: Small diagonal right pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiamond.description: Small diamond pattern is applied to the data item.

smallTriangle.description: Small triangle pattern is applied to the data item.

pieSliceExplode.description: A number from 0 to 1 indicating the amount to explode the pie slice. Only applies to pie charts.

shortDesc.description: The description of this series. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text on the corresponding legend item for the series.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

stackCategory.description: In stacked charts, groups series together for stacking. All series without a stackCategory will be assigned to the same stack.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgClassName is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgStyle is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

type.description: The type of data objects to display for this series. Only applies to bar, line, area, stock, box plot, and combo charts.

area.description: Series will be represented by an area. Use lineWithArea to prevent values from being obscured.

auto.description: Series type will be inherited from chart type.

bar.description: Series will be represented by a bar.

boxPlot.description: Series will be represented by box plot markers. This is only supported for stock charts.

candlestick.description: Series will be represented by candlestick markers. This is only supported for stock charts.

line.description: Series will be represented by a line.

lineWithArea.description: Series will be presented by a line and area.

seriesComparator.description: A comparator function that determines the ordering of the chart series when using a DataProvider. If undefined, the series will follow the order in which they are found in the data.

sorting.description: Specifies the sorting of the data. It should only be used for pie charts, bar/line/area charts with one series, or stacked bar/area charts. Sorting will not apply when using a hierarchical group axis.

ascending.description: Data items are sorted in ascending order.

descending.description: Data items are sorted in descending order.

off.description: Groups are sorted in the order they are discovered in the data.

splitDualY.description: Defines whether the plot area is split into two sections, so that sets of data assigned to the different Y-axes appear in different parts of the plot area. Stock charts do not support "off".

auto.description: Plot area will not be split into two sections except for the stock charts.

off.description: Plot area will not be split into two sections.

on.description: Plot area will be split into two sections corresponding to datasets assigned to the different Y-axes.

splitterPosition.description: In a split dual-Y chart, specifies the fraction of the space that is given to the Y-axis subchart. Valid values are numbers from 0 to 1.

stack.description: Defines whether the data items are stacked. Only applies to bar, line, area, and combo charts. Does not apply to range series.

off.description: Data items will not be stacked.

on.description: Data items belonging to same group will be stacked.

stackLabel.description: Defines whether the total values of stacked data items should be displayed. Only applies to bar charts. See the Help documentation for more information.

off.description: The total value of the stacked data items will not be displayed.

on.description: The total value of the stacked data items will be displayed.

stackLabelProvider.description: A function that returns a custom stack label. The function takes a context argument, provided by the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

styleDefaults.description: An object defining the default styles for series colors, marker shapes, and other style attributes. Properties specified on this object may be overridden by specifications on the data object.

animationDownColor.description: The color of the indicator shown for a decreasing data change animation.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

animationIndicators.description: Defines whether data change indicators are displayed during animation.

all.description: Data change indicators will be enabled.

none.description: Data change indicators will be disabled.

animationUpColor.description: The color of the indicator shown for an increasing data change animation.

barGapRatio.description: Specifies the width of the bar group gap as a ratio of the group width. The valid value is a number from 0 to 1.

borderColor.description: The default border color for the data items. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The default border width for the data items. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot items.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems.

colors.description: The array defining the default color ramp for the series.

dataCursor.description: An object defining the data cursor style.

lineColor.description: The color of the data cursor line.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data cursor line.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data cursor line in pixels.

markerColor.description: The color of the data cursor marker. Defaults to the data series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Whether the data cursor marker is displayed. Marker should only be hidden if the data cursor is displaying information for the entire group.

off.description: Data cursor marker will not be displayed.

on.description: Data cursor marker will be displayed.

markerSize.description: The size of the data cursor marker in pixels.

dataItemGaps.description: Specifies the presence and size of the gaps between data items, such as bars, markers, and areas. Valid values are a percentage string from 0% to 100%, where 100% produces the maximum supported gaps.

dataLabelCollision.description: Rule for adjusting data label layout. See the Help documentation for more information.

fitInBounds.description: Data label positions will be adjusted in order to fit in the plot area.

none.description: No data label positions will be adjusted to fit in the plot area. Labels may flow outside the plot area.

dataLabelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

aboveMarker.description: Label will be placed above the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

afterMarker.description: Label will be placed after the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

auto.description: For un-stacked bar charts, 'auto' will act as 'insideBarEdge'. For other chart types, 'auto' will act as 'center'.

beforeMarker.description: Label will be placed before the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

belowMarker.description: Label will be placed below the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

center.description: Label will be placed in the center of the data marker.

insideBarEdge.description: Label will be placed inside the bar edge. Only applies to non polar bar series.

none.description: No data label is shown.

outsideBarEdge.description: Label will be placed outside the bar edge. Only applies to non polar bar series.

outsideSlice.description: Label will be placed outside the chart. Only applies to pie chart.

dataLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

funnelBackgroundColor.description: The default background color of funnel slices that show actual/target values.

groupSeparators.description: An object defining the style for hierarchical label separators.

color.description: The color of the separators lines.

rendered.description: Defines whether the group separators are displayed.

auto.description: Group separators in hierarchical axis will be displayed.

off.description: Group separators in hierarchical axis will not be displayed.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting items in chart.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Defaults to none for scatter and bubble charts otherwise line type is straight.

centeredSegmented.description: Data points will be connected with a centered segmented line.

centeredStepped.description: Data points will be connected with a centered stepped line.

curved.description: Data points will be connected with a curved line.

none.description: Data points will not be connected.

segmented.description: Data points will be connected with a segmented line.

stepped.description: Data points will be connected with a stepped line.

straight.description: Data points will be connected with a straight line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data markers should be displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

auto.description: Data markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

off.description: Data markers will not be displayed.

on.description: Data markers will be displayed.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data marker shape will be based on chart type.

circle.description: Data markers will be circular in shape.

diamond.description: Data markers will be diamond in shape.

human.description: Data markers will be human in shape.

plus.description: Data markers will be plus in shape.

square.description: Data markers will be square in shape.

star.description: Data markers will be star in shape.

triangleDown.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing down.

triangleUp.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing up.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers in pixels.

marqueeBorderColor.description: The border color of the marquee. Applies to marquee selection and marquee zoom.

marqueeColor.description: The fill color of the marquee. Applies to marquee selection and marquee zoom.

maxBarWidth.description: Specifies the maximum width of each bar in pixels.

otherColor.description: Specifies the color of the "Other" slice. Only applies to pie chart.

patterns.description: The array defining the default pattern ramp for the series. This is used only when seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

pieFeelerColor.description: The color of the line extending from the pie slice to the slice label.

pieInnerRadius.description: Specifies the radius of the inner circle that can be used to create a donut chart. Valid values range from 0 (default) to 1. Not supported if 3D effect is on.

selectionEffect.description: The selection effect that is applied to selected items. The values explode and highlightAndExplode only apply to pie charts.

explode.description: Selected data items will have an explode effect.

highlight.description: Selected data items will be highlighted.

highlightAndExplode.description: Selected data items will have both the highligt and explode effect.

seriesEffect.description: Defines the fill effect for the data items.

color.description: Data items will be filled with solid colors.

gradient.description: Data items will have a gradient.

pattern.description: Data items will be filled with colored patterns.

shapes.description: The array defining the default shape ramp for the series. Valid values are defined in the markerShape attribute.

stackLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the stack label.

stockFallingColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the candlestick when the 'open' value is greater than the 'close' value.

stockRangeColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the range bars for candlestick.

stockRisingColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the candlestick when the 'close' value is greater than the 'open' value.

stockVolumeColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the volume bars. If specified, overrides the default rising and falling colors used by the volume bars.

threeDEffect.description: Defines whether the chart is displayed with a 3D effect. Only applies to pie, funnel and pyramid charts.

off.description: Chart will not be displayed with a 3D effect.

on.description: Chart will be displayed with a 3D effect.

tooltipLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the labels in the tooltip.

tooltipValueStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the values in the tooltip.

timeAxisType.description: The type of time axis to display in the chart. Time axis is only supported for Cartesian bar, line, area, stock, box plot, and combo charts. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Time axis is disabled unless it is a stock chart, for which the timeAxisType is mixedFrequency.

disabled.description: Time axis is disabled.

enabled.description: The time value for each data item is passed using the group-id attribute of oj-chart-item. The time intervals do not have to be uniform. Data items from the same group should have the same time value.

mixedFrequency.description: The time value for each data item is passed using the x attribute of oj-chart-item. The time intervals do not have to be uniform. Data item from the same group can have different time values.

skipGaps.description: The time value for each data item is passed using the group-id attribute of oj-chart-item. The times will always be drawn uniformly ignoring gaps. Data items from the same group should have the same time value.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip for chart. The function takes a context argument, provided by the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

touchResponse.description: Specifies configuration options for touch and hold delays on mobile devices. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Chart will behave like touchStart if it determines that it is not rendered within scrolling content and if panning is not available for those elements that support the feature.

touchStart.description: Chart will instantly trigger the touch gesture and consume the page pan events if it does not require an internal feature that requires a touch start gesture like panning, zooming, or when marquee selection is initiated.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleContainsControls.description: Used to describe a container that contains controls.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelClearSelection.description: Text shown for clearing multiple selection on touch devices.

labelClose.description: Used for the close value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

labelDataVisualization.description: Label for data visualizations used for accessibility.

labelDate.description: Used for the date value in the tooltip, if a time axis is being used.

labelDefaultGroupName.description: Used when the group names are not specified.

labelHigh.description: >Used for the high value in the tooltip for stock and range data.

labelInvalidData.description: Text shown when the component receives invalid data.

labelLow.description: Used for the low value in the tooltip for stock and range data.

labelNoData.description: Text shown when the component receives no data.

labelOpen.description: Used for the open value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelOther.description: Used for the other series label which aggregates small data values.

labelPercentage.description: Used for displaying the percentage in the tooltip.

labelQ1.description: Used for displaying the first quartile for box plots.

labelQ2.description: Used for displaying the second quartile (i.e. median) for box plots.

labelQ3.description: Used for displaying the third quartile for box plots.

labelTargetValue.description: Used for the funnel chart target value.

labelValue.description: Used for the data item value in the tooltip.

labelVolume.description: Used for the volume value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelX.description: Used for the x value in the tooltip.

labelY.description: Used for the y value in the tooltip.

labelZ.description: Used for the z value in the tooltip.

stateCollapsed.description: Used to describe the collapsed state for accessibility.

stateDrillable.description: Used to describe a drillable object for accessibility.

stateExpanded.description: Used to describe the expanded state for accessibility.

stateHidden.description: Used to describe the hidden state for accessibility.

stateIsolated.description: Used to describe the isolated state for accessibility.

stateMaximized.description: Used to describe the maximized state for accessibility.

stateMinimized.description: Used to describe the minimized state for accessibility.

stateSelected.description: Used to describe the selected state for accessibility.

stateUnselected.description: Used to describe the unselected state for accessibility.

stateVisible.description: Used to describe the visible state for accessibility.

tooltipSelect.description: Used for the marquee select tooltip.

tooltipZoom.description: Used for the marquee zoom tooltip.

type.description: Specifies the chart type. See the Help documentation for more information.

area.description: Series will be represented by an area. Use lineWithArea to prevent values from being obscured.

bar.description: Data items will be represented by bars.

boxPlot.description: Series will be represented by box plot markers.

bubble.description: Data items will be represented as bubble markers with x, y, and z values. z value defines the relative size of the bubbles.

combo.description: Multiple series can be represented with multiple types of markers: bar, line and area.

funnel.description: Data items are represented as funnel slices.

line.description: Series will be represented by a line.

lineWithArea.description: Series will be presented by a line and area.

pie.description: Data items are represented as pie slices.

pyramid.description: Data items are represented as pyramid slices.

scatter.description: Data items will be represented as markers with x and y values.

stock.description: Series will be represented by candlestick markers. There are other representations available like area, bar, line and line with area.

valueFormats.description: An object specifying value formatting and tooltip behavior, whose keys generally correspond to the attribute names on the data items.

close.description: Specifies the value formatting and tooltip behavior for the close values of a stock chart.

converter.description: The converter used to format the label. See the Help documentation for more information.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the value. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

auto.description: Chart chooses the scaling based on the data.

billion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to billion based on locale.

million.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to million based on locale.

none.description: Values will not be scaled with any suffix.

quadrillion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to quadrillion based on locale.

thousand.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to thousand based on locale.

trillion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to trillion based on locale.

tooltipDisplay.description: Whether the value is displayed in the tooltip.

tooltipLabel.description: A string representing the label that is displayed before the value in the tooltip.

group.description: Specifies tooltip behavior for the groups.

tooltipDisplay.description: Whether the value is displayed in the tooltip.

auto.description: Value will be displayed in the tooltip.

off.description: Value will not be displayed in the tooltip.

tooltipLabel.description: A string representing the label that is displayed before the value in the tooltip. This value can also take an array of strings to be applied to hierarchical group names, from outermost to innermost.

high.description: Specifies the value formatting and tooltip behavior for the high values.

xAxis.description: An object defining properties for the axis, tick marks, tick labels, and axis titles.

axisLine.description: An object defining properties for the axis line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line.

rendered.description: Defines whether the line is rendered.

auto.description: Axis line will not be rendered for y and y2 axis of bar, area, line, and combo charts.

off.description: Axis line will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis line will be rendered.

baselineScaling.description: Defines whether the axis baseline starts at the minimum value of the data or at zero. Only applies to numerical data axes.

min.description: Baseline starts at the minimum value of the data.

dataMax.description: The maximum data value corresponding to an axis. If specified, the automatic axis extent calculation will use this value. Only applies to numerical axes.

dataMin.description: The minimum data value corresponding to an axis. If specified, the automatic axis extent calculation will use this value. Only applies to numerical axes.

majorTick.description: An object defining properties for the major tick marks.

baselineColor.description: The color of the major tick mark at the baseline. Valid values are auto, inherit, or a custom color. If set to inherit, it will follow the lineColor attribute.

auto.description: Default value according to theme is used.

inherit.description: Axis baseline color will be same as lineColor.

baselineStyle.description: The line style of the major tick mark at the baseline. If not specified, it will follow the lineStyle attribute.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

baselineWidth.description: The width of the major tick mark at the baseline. If not specified, it will follow the lineWidth attribute.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the tick marks.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line.

rendered.description: Defines whether the line is rendered.

auto.description: Axis line will not be rendered for y and y2 axis of bar, area, line, and combo charts.

off.description: Axis line will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis line will be rendered.

max.description: The maximum value of the axis. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

maxSize.description: Defines the maximum size of the axis in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

min.description: The minimum value of the axis. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

minStep.description: The minimum increment between major tick marks. This is typically used to prevent fractional axis values for discrete measures. Only applies to numerical axes.

minorStep.description: The increment between minor tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. Only applies to numerical axes. See the Help documentation for more information.

minorTick.description: An object defining properties for the minor tick marks.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the tick marks.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line.

rendered.description: Defines whether the line is rendered.

auto.description: Axis line will not be rendered for y and y2 axis of bar, area, line, and combo charts.

off.description: Axis line will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis line will be rendered.

referenceObjects.description: The array of reference objects associated with the axis.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this reference object. This allows highlighting and filtering of a reference object through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the reference object id is used.

color.description: The color of the reference object.

displayInLegend.description: Defines whether the reference object should be shown in the legend.

off.description: Reference object will not be shown in the legend.

on.description: Reference object will be shown in the legend.

high.description: The high value of an area reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The id of the reference object.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the line reference object. Does not apply to area reference objects.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line reference object. Does not apply to area reference objects.

location.description: The location of the reference object relative to the data items.

back.description: Reference object is rendered behind the data items.

front.description: Reference object is rendered in front of data items.

low.description: The low value of an area reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

text.description: The text displayed in the legend for the reference object.

type.description: The type of reference object being shown. See the Help documentation for more information.

value.description: The value of a line reference object. This property defines a constant value across the entire reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines whether the axis is rendered.

off.description: Axis will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis will be rendered.

scale.description: Defines the axis scale. Only applies to numerical axes.

linear.description: Axis values will follow a linear scale.

log.description: Axis values will follow a log scale.

size.description: Defines the size of the axis in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

step.description: The increment between major tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. Only applies to time and numerical axes. See the Help documentation for more information.

converter.description: The converter used to format the labels. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines whether the tick labels are rendered.

off.description: Axis tick labels will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis tick labels will be rendered.

rotation.description: Defines whether the chart will automatically rotate the labels by 90 degrees in order to fit more labels on the axis. The rotation will only be applied to categorical labels for a horizontal axis.

auto.description: Labels will automatically rotate by 90 degree in order to fit more labels on the axis if needed.

none.description: Labels will not be rotated in order to fit more labels on the axis.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the labels. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

auto.description: Chart chooses the scaling based on the data.

billion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to billion based on locale.

million.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to million based on locale.

none.description: Values will not be scaled with any suffix.

quadrillion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to quadrillion based on locale.

thousand.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to thousand based on locale.

trillion.description: Values will be scaled with suffix corresponding to trillion based on locale.

style.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the labels.

title.description: The axis title. Does not apply to polar charts.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the axis title.

viewportEndGroup.description: Specifies the end group of the current viewport. Only applies to charts with group or time axis. If not specified, the default end group is the last group in the data set.

viewportMax.description: Specifies the maximum x coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. See the Help documentation for more information.

viewportMin.description: Specifies the minimum x coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. See the Help documentation for more information.

viewportStartGroup.description: Specifies the start group of the current viewport. Only applies to charts with group or time axis. If not specified, the default start group is the first group in the data set.

y2Axis.description: An object defining properties for the axis, tick marks, tick labels, and axis titles. Y2 axis is only supported for Cartesian bar, line, area, and combo charts.

off.description: Tick marks of y1 and y2 axes may not be aligned.

on.description: Tick marks of y1 and y2 axes will be aligned.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line.

off.description: Axis line will not be rendered.

on.description: Axis line will be rendered.

min.description: Baseline starts at the minimum value of the data.

dataMin.description: The minimum data value corresponding to an axis. If specified, the automatic axis extent calculation will use this value. Only applies to numerical axes.

majorTick.description: An object defining properties for the major tick marks.

inherit.description: Axis baseline color will be same as lineColor.

baselineStyle.description: The line style of the major tick mark at the baseline. If not specified, it will follow the lineStyle attribute.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

baselineWidth.description: The width of the major tick mark at the baseline. If not specified, it will follow the lineWidth attribute.

bottom.description: The axis will be placed at the bottom of the chart. Only applies to horizontal charts.

end.description: The axis will be placed at end of the chart. Only applies to vertical charts.

start.description: The axis will be placed at start of the chart. Only applies to vertical charts.

top.description: The axis will be placed at the top of the chart. Only applies to horizontal charts.

id.description: the id of the drilled object

series.description: the series id of the drilled object, if applicable

group.description: the group id of the drilled object, if applicable

data.description: the data object of the drilled item

borderColor.description: The border color of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot item.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend or other visualization elements. If not defined, series categories are used.

close.description: The close value for stock candlestick. When bar, line, or area series type are used on a stock chart, this value is displayed.

color.description: The color of the data item. This color value is not inherited by chart legend. See chart series color and display-in-legend for more details.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

inherit.description: Drilling behavior will be inherited from the chart.

off.description: Drilling will not be enabled for the data item.

on.description: Drilling will be enabled for the data item.

high.description: The high value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

id.description: The id of the chart item. This id will be provided as part of the context for events on the chart.

items.description: An array of nested data items to be used for defining the markers for outliers or additional data items of a box plot.

label.description: The label for the data item. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. Not supported for box plot or candlestick.

labelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

aboveMarker.description: Label will be placed above the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

afterMarker.description: Label will be placed after the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

auto.description: For un-stacked bar charts, 'auto' will act as 'insideBarEdge'. For other chart types, 'auto' will act as 'center'.

beforeMarker.description: Label will be placed before the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

belowMarker.description: Label will be placed below the data marker. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series.

center.description: Label will be placed in the center of the data marker.

insideBarEdge.description: Label will be placed inside the bar edge. Only applies to non polar bar series.

none.description: No data label is shown.

outsideBarEdge.description: Label will be placed outside the bar edge. Only applies to non polar bar series.

outsideSlice.description: Label will be placed outside the chart. Only applies to pie chart.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

low.description: The low value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

auto.description: Data markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

off.description: Data marker will be displayed.

on.description: Data marker will not be displayed.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data marker shape will be based on chart type.

circle.description: Data markers will be circular in shape.

diamond.description: Data markers will be diamond in shape.

human.description: Data markers will be human in shape.

plus.description: Data markers will be plus in shape.

square.description: Data markers will be square in shape.

star.description: Data markers will be star in shape.

triangleDown.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing down.

triangleUp.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing up.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers. Only applies to line, area, and scatter series. Does not apply to bubble charts, which calculate marker size based on the z values.

open.description: The open value for stock candlestick.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the data item. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

auto.description: No pattern is applied to data item fill.

largeChecker.description: Large checker pattern is applied to the data item.

largeCrosshatch.description: Large cross hatch pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiagonalLeft.description: Large diagonal left pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiagonalRight.description: Large diagonal right pattern is applied to the data item.

largeDiamond.description: Large diamond pattern is applied to the data item.

largeTriangle.description: Large triangle pattern is applied to the data item.

smallChecker.description: Small checker pattern is applied to the data item.

smallCrosshatch.description: Small cross hatch pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiagonalLeft.description: Small diagonal left pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiagonalRight.description: Small diagonal right pattern is applied to the data item.

smallDiamond.description: Small diamond pattern is applied to the data item.

smallTriangle.description: Small triangle pattern is applied to the data item.

q1.description: The first quartile value for box plot.

q2.description: The second quartile (median) value for box plot.

q3.description: The third quartile value for box plot.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. Will be lazily created if a function is used.This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over marker-shape.

targetValue.description: The target value for a funnel chart. When this is set, the value attribute defines the filled area within the slice and this represents the value of the whole slice.

value.description: The value for this data item. Corresponding to the y value for bar, line, area, and combo charts and the slice values for pie, funnel and pyramid charts. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

itemData.description: the row data object of the drilled item. This will only be set if a DataProvider is being used.

seriesData.description: the data for the series of the drilled object

areaColor.description: The area color of the series. Only applies if series type is area or lineWithArea.

assignedToY2.description: Defines whether the series is associated with the y2 axis. Only applies to Cartesian bar, line, area, and combo charts.

off.description: The series is not associated with the y2 axis.

on.description: The series is associated with the y2 axis.

borderColor.description: The border color of the series.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the series.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

solid.description: Line will have a solid stroke.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Default value depending on series type.

centeredSegmented.description: Data points will be connected with a centered segmented line.

centeredStepped.description: Data points will be connected with a centered stepped line.

curved.description: Data points will be connected with a curved line.

none.description: Data points will not be connected.

segmented.description: Data points will be connected with a segmented line.

stepped.description: Data points will be connected with a stepped line.

straight.description: Data points will be connected with a straight line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

off.description: Data markers belonging to the series will not be displayed.

on.description: Data markers belonging to the series will be displayed.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Data marker shape will be based on chart type.

circle.description: Data markers will be circular in shape.

diamond.description: Data markers will be diamond in shape.

human.description: Data markers will be human in shape.

plus.description: Data markers will be plus in shape.

square.description: Data markers will be square in shape.

star.description: Data markers will be star in shape.

triangleDown.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing down.

triangleUp.description: Data markers will be of a triangular shape facing up.

scrollPolicy.description: Specifies how data are fetched as user scrolls through the data grid.

auto.description: the DataGrid will decide the scroll policy

loadMoreOnScroll.description: additional data are fetched when the user scrolls to the bottom of the DataGrid and all previous data are kept in the DOM.

scroll.description: virtual scrolling is used meaning only rows/columns visible in the viewport are fetched and kept in the DOM

scrollPolicyOptions.description: Specifies fetch options for scrolling behaviors that trigger data fetches.

maxColumnCount.description: The maximum number of columns to display before fetching more data rows will be stopped.

maxRowCount.description: The maximum number of rows to display before fetching more data rows will be stopped.

scrollPosition.description: Specifies the current scroll position of the data grid. See the Help documentation for more information.

columnIndex.description: The zero-based column index of the cell at the origin of the grid. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

columnKey.description: The column key of the cell at the origin of the grid. If DataGridDataSource is used for data and the key does not exist in the DataGridDataSource, then the value is ignored. If it is unknown in the data source then the grid will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the axis is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

offsetX.description: The horizontal offset in pixel relative to the cell identified by key/index.

offsetY.description: The vertical offset in pixel relative to the cell identified by key/index.

rowIndex.description: The zero-based row index of the cell at the origin of the grid. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

rowKey.description: The row key of the cell at the origin of the grid. If DataGridDataSource is used for data and the key does not exist in the DataGridDataSource, then the value is ignored. If it is unknown in the data source then the grid will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the axis is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

x.description: The horizontal position in pixels.

y.description: The vertical position in pixels.

scrollToKey.description: Specifies the behavior when DataGrid needs to scroll to a position based on a row/column key.

always.description: DataGrid will scroll to a position based on row/column key as long as the row/column keys are valid.

auto.description: The behavior is determined by the component. By default the behavior is the same as "capability" except when the deprecated DataGridDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "always".

capability.description: DataGrid will only scroll to a position based on row/column key if either the cell has already been fetched or if the associated DataProvider supports 'immediate' for 'iterationSpeed' capability.

never.description: DataGrid will not change the scroll position if the request is based on a row/column key.

fit.description: Shift the element away from the edge of the window.

flip.description: Flip the element to the opposite side of the target and the collision detection is run again to see if it will fit. Whichever side allows more of the element to be visible will be used.

flipfit.description: First applies the flip logic, placing the element on whichever side allows more of the element to be visible. Then the fit logic is applied to ensure as much of the element is visible as possible.

none.description: No collision detection.

my.description: Defines which edge on the dialog to align with the target ("of") element.

end.description: evaluates to "right" in LTR mode and "left" in RTL mode.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

of.description: Specifies which element to position the dialog against. See the Help documentation for more information.

offset.description: Defines a point offset in pixels from the ("my") alignment.

x.description: Horizontal alignment offset.

y.description: Vertical alignment offset.

resizeBehavior.description: Specifies the resizeBehavior of the dialog. See the Help documentation for more information.

none.description: The dialog will not be interactively resizable.

resizable.description: The dialog will be interactively resizable.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

labelCloseIcon.description: Label for the dialog close button.

close.description: Closes the dialog.

ojClose.description: Triggered after the dialog is dismissed via the close() method.

ojFocus.description: Triggered after focus has been transferred to the dialog.

ojOpen.description: Triggered after the dialog is launched via the open() method.

ojResize.description: Triggered when the dialog is being resized. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-file-picker.name: oj-file-picker
oj-file-picker.description: A file picker displays a clickable dropzone for selecting files from the device storage.

styleClasses.description: Apply to a custom file picker if the entire dropzone is replaced with another clickable element like button or menu item.
Apply to the dropzone of the file picker.
Apply to the dropzone text of the file picker.

styleClasses.name: oj-filepicker-custom
styleClasses.description:
Apply to a custom file picker if the entire dropzone is replaced with another clickable element like button or menu item.
Note that the oj-filepicker-custom class doesn't have to be specified in order to change the dropzone text.

styleClasses.description: Apply to the dropzone of the file picker.

accept.description: An array of strings of allowed MIME types or file extensions that can be uploaded. If not specified, accept all file types

capture.description: Specifies the preferred facing mode for the device's media capture mechanism.

user.description: Specifies user-facing as the preferred mode

environment.description: Specifies environment-facing as the preferred mode

implementation.description: Specifies an implementation-specific default as the preferred facing mode

none.description: No capture mechanism is used

disabled.description: Disables the filepicker if set to true

primaryText.description: The primary text for the default file picker.

secondaryText.description: The secondary text for the default file picker.

selectOn.description: The type of event to select the files.

status.description: Main use case was to turn off drag and drop for button filepicker.  The current recommendation for that use case is to use ojfilepickerutils with an oj-button.

auto.description: either click or drag and drop to select the files

clickAndDrop.description: either click or drag and drop to select the files

drop.description: drag and drop the files

selectionMode.description: Whether to allow single or multiple file selection.

trigger.description: The trigger slot is used to replace the default content of the file picker.

ojBeforeSelect.description: Triggered before files are selected to allow for custom validation

accept.description: This method can be called with an application-created Promise to cancel this event asynchronously.  The Promise should be resolved or rejected to accept or cancel the event, respectively.

ojInvalidSelect.description: Triggered when invalid files are selected

messages.description: Messages that should be displayed to the user (e.g. in an oj-messages component) describing invalid files.

until.description: This property may be populated with a Promise to provide short-term feedback during a user interaction (typically drag and drop); the feedback should be cleared upon the resolution of this Promise.

ojSelect.description: Triggered after the files are selected

files.description: The files that were just selected.

oj-film-strip.name: oj-film-strip
oj-film-strip.description: A filmstrip lays out its children in a single row or column across logical pages and allows navigating through them.

arrowPlacement.description: Specifies the placement of the navigation arrows.

adjacent.description: Arrows are outside, adjacent to the filmStrip content. The arrows are still inside the bounds of the filmStrip element itself.

overlay.description: Arrows are inside, overlaying the filmStrip content.

arrowVisibility.description: Specifies the visibility of the navigation arrows.

auto.description: Behaves as if the value were visible when the arrow-placement attribute is set to adjacent, and hover when the arrow-placement attribute is set to overlay.

hover.description: Arrows are visible when the mouse is over the filmStrip, and hidden otherwise.

currentItem.description: Specifies the child item whose logical page should be displayed.

id.description: string id of the item

index.description: numeric 0-based index of the item

off.description: Navigation is bounded between first and last page and can't go any further in the direction of navigation.

page.description: Navigation is not bounded between first and last page and can go further in the direction of navigation. This lets the user loop around from first page to last page, or from last page to first page.

maxItemsPerPage.description: Specifies the maximum number of child items shown in a logical page.

orientation.description: Specifies the orientation of the FilmStrip.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

labelAccArrowNextPage.description: Accessible label for the next page navigation arrow.

labelAccArrowPreviousPage.description: Accessible label for the previous page navigation arrow.

labelAccFilmStrip.description: Accessible page information label for the filmstrip element.

tipArrowNextPage.description: Tooltip for the next page navigation arrow.

tipArrowPreviousPage.description: Tooltip for the previous page navigation arrow.

getItemsPerPage.description: Get the actual number of items shown per logical page.

getPagingModel.description: Get the PagingModel created and used by the FilmStrip.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

styleClasses.description: In Redwood by default a form layout has a max width, add this class if you'd like to opt out and have the form layout to stretch the full width.

styleClasses.name: oj-formlayout-full-width
styleClasses.description: In Redwood by default a form layout has a max width, add this class if you'd like to opt out and have the form layout to stretch the full width.

styleVariables.description: Bottom margin of each row in a form layout

oj-form-layout.description: A form layout manages the layout of labels and fields in a form.

colspanWrap.description: Specifies how to fit components with colspan attribute in the form layout, when there are fewer columns left in the current row than the colspan value specifies.

nowrap.description: The component will occupy the remaining columns in the current row.

wrap.description: The component will start from the first column of the next row.

columns.description: Specifies the exact number of columns. This attribute overrides max-columns if it is positive.

direction.description: Specifies the layout direction of the form layout children.

column.description: Components are laid out in columns

row.description: Components are laid out in rows

labelEdge.description: Specifies how the label is created and aligned with its form control. See the Help documentation for more information.

inside.description: oj-form-layout will not create any label. Label will be created by the form control if the form control has its label-edge set to "inside". Please see the specific form control's label-edge attribute documentation for details.

start.description: oj-form-layout will create a label that's before the start of the form control if the form control's label-edge is not explicitly set. If the form control specifies "inside" or "none" as its label-edge, no label will be created by oj-form-layout.

top.description: oj-form-layout will create a label that's on top of the form control if the form controls label-edge is not explicitly set. If the form control specifies "inside" or "none" as its label-edge, no label will be created by oj-form-layout.

labelWidth.description: Specifies the label width. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelWrapping.description: Specifies if the label text should wrap or truncate.

maxColumns.description: Specifies the maximum number of columns. See the Help documentation for more information.

readonly.description: Specifies whether the form is readonly. See the Help documentation for more information.

userAssistanceDensity.description: Specifies the density of the form component's user assistance presentation.

compact.description: messages, help, hints, and required will not be shown inline; they will show in a mode that keeps the screen more compact, like a popup for the messages, and a required icon to indicate Required.

efficient.description: messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with reserved space underneath.

reflow.description: If reflow, messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with no reserved space.

oj-gantt-dependency.name: oj-gantt-dependency
oj-gantt-dependency.description: The oj-gantt-dependency element is used to declare properties for gantt dependency lines. See the Help documentation for more information.

predecessorTaskId.description: The identifier for the predecessor task. This must reference a task in Gantt.

shortDesc.description: The description of the dependency line. This is used for accessibility.

successorTaskId.description: The identifier for the successor task. This must reference a task in Gantt.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes to apply to the dependency line.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the dependency line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

type.description: The type of dependency.

finishFinish.description: predecessor task must finish before successor task can finish

finishStart.description: predecessor task must finish before successor task can start

startFinish.description: predecessor task must start before successor task can finish

startStart.description: predecessor task must start before successor task can start

oj-gantt-reference-object.name: oj-gantt-reference-object
oj-gantt-reference-object.description: The oj-gantt-reference-object element is used to declare properties for gantt row reference objects. See the Help documentation for more information.

end.description: The end time value of this reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

start.description: The start time value of this reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the reference object. Note that only CSS style applicable to SVG elements can be used.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the reference object. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

oj-gantt-row.name: oj-gantt-row
oj-gantt-row.description: The oj-gantt-row element is used to declare properties for gantt rows. See the Help documentation for more information.

label.description: The label associated with the row.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the label. Only CSS style applicable to SVG elements can be used. See the Help documentation for more information.

referenceObjects.description: The reference objects associated with the row. This is optional and is only used if data is set using row-data attribute.

shortDesc.description: The description of the row. This is used for accessibility.

tasks.description: The tasks associated with the row. This is required if data is set using row-data attribute.

oj-gantt-task.name: oj-gantt-task
oj-gantt-task.description: The oj-gantt-task element is used to declare properties for gantt tasks. See the Help documentation for more information.

attribute.description: Specifies the attribute of the task.

rendered.description: Specifies whether the attribute bar is rendered.

shortDesc.description: The description of the attribute.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the attribute.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the attribute.

baseline.description: Specifies the baseline of the task. When only one of 'start' or 'end' value is specified, or when 'start' and 'end' values are equal, the baseline is considered a milestone baseline.

borderRadius.description: The border radius of the baseline. Accepts values allowed in CSS border-radius attribute.

end.description: The end time of the baseline. See the Help documentation for more information.

height.description: The height of the baseline in pixels.

start.description: The start time of the baseline. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the baseline.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the baseline.

borderRadius.description: The border radius of the task. Accepts valid CSS border-radius attribute values.

downtime.description: Specifies the downtime of the task.

end.description: The end time of the downtime. See the Help documentation for more information.

start.description: The start time of the downtime. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the downtime.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the downtime.

end.description: The task end time. See the Help documentation for more information.

height.description: The task height, in pixels. See the Help documentation for more information.

label.description: The label associated with the task.

labelPosition.description: The position of the label relative to the task. An array of values is also supported. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

overlap.description: Configures the placement of this task relative to a task it overlaps with.

behavior.description: Specifies the behavior when a task overlaps a chronologically previous adjacent tasks. See the Help documentation for more information.

overtime.description: Specifies the overtime of the task.

end.description: The end time of the overtime. See the Help documentation for more information.

start.description: The start time of the overtime. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the overtime.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the overtime.

progress.description: Specifies the progress of the task. This property is ignored if the task is a milestone.

borderRadius.description: The border radius of the progress bar. Accepts valid CSS border-radius attribute values.

height.description: Specifies the height of the progress bar in pixels or as a percentage of the associated task bar height. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes to apply to the progress bar.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the progress bar.

value.description: The progress value, between 0 and 1 inclusive. If not specified or invalid, no progress bar will be shown.

status.description: Set the data using the row-data attribute instead of task-data, and specify task-id instead of this attribute.

rowId.description: The id for the row the task belongs to. This is required if data is set using task-data attribute.

shortDesc.description: The description of the task. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text.

start.description: The task start time. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes defining the style of the task.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the task.

taskId.description: The id of the task. This is required if data is set using row-data attribute.

type.description: Defines the task type to be rendered. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-gantt.name: oj-gantt
oj-gantt.description: A gantt displays scheduling information graphically, making it easier to plan, coordinate, and track various tasks and resources.

animationOnDataChange.description: Defines the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Defines the animation that is shown on initial display.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the dependencyTemplate, taskTemplate, or rowTemplate slots.

axisPosition.description: The position of the major and minor axis.

dependencies.description: An array of objects that defines dependencies between tasks. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The identifier for the dependency line. This must be unique across all dependency lines in Gantt. The id should be set by the application if the dependency-data DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the case.

predecessorTaskId.description: The identifier for the predecessor task. This must reference a task in Gantt.

shortDesc.description: The description of the dependency line. This is used for accessibility.

successorTaskId.description: The identifier for the successor task. This must reference a task in Gantt.

svgClassName.description: A space delimited list of CSS style classes to apply to the dependency line.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style defining the style of the dependency line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

type.description: The type of dependency.

finishFinish.description: predecessor task must finish before successor task can finish

finishStart.description: predecessor task must finish before successor task can start

startFinish.description: predecessor task must start before successor task can finish

startStart.description: predecessor task must start before successor task can start

dependencyData.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the dependencies of the Gantt. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

dependencyLineShape.description: Specifies the shape of the dependency lines.

move.description: Defines a subset of high level configurations for moving elements to another location within the Gantt.

tasks.description: Enable or disable moving the non-baseline portions of selected tasks to a different location within the same Gantt.

disabled.description: Disable moving selected tasks

dragMode.description: Specifies the action that is performed when a drag occurs.

end.description: The end time of the Gantt. See the Help documentation for more information.

expanded.description: Specifies the key set of ids for expanded Gantt items.

gridlines.description: An object specifying whether to display or hide the horizontal and vertical grid lines.

horizontal.description: Specifies whether to show horizontal gridlines.

vertical.description: Specifies whether to show vertical gridlines.

majorAxis.description: Specifies the major time axis. If not specified, no major time axis is shown.

status.description: this value will be removed in the future

converter.description: An object used to format the major axis labels. See the Help documentation for more information.

days.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'days' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

default.description: The default converter (an object literal or instance that duck types Converter) to use for all 'scale' values that do not otherwise have a converter object provided. See also DateTimeConverter.

hours.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'hours' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

minutes.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'minutes' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

months.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'months' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

quarters.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'quarters' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

seconds.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'seconds' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

weeks.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'weeks' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

years.description: A converter (an instance that duck types Converter) used to format the 'years' scale. If not specified, the default converter will be used for this scale. See also DateTimeConverter.

height.description: Specifies the major axis height in pixels. See the Help documentation for more information.

scale.description: Specifies the major axis time scale.

zoomOrder.description: An array of scales used for zooming from longest to shortest. See the Help documentation for more information.

minorAxis.description: Specifies the minor time axis. This is required for the Gantt to render properly.

status.description: this value will be removed in the future

auto.description: The component will determine the best mobile virtual keyboard to use. For example, it may look at the converter's resolvedOptions to determine if it formats using non-numeric characters or not. If it formats using non-numeric characters, like oj-input-number's default converter for 'en-US' loocale (1000 formats to "1,000"), then it will use "text".

number.description: Use a mobile virtual keyboard for entering numbers. If using "number", you must set the converter attribute to a converter that formats to numeric characters only, otherwise the value will not be shown. The reason for this is oj-input-number uses the browser native input type='number' and when you set an input value that contains a non-numeric character, browsers do not display the value. For example, "1,000" would not be shown. And oj-input-number's default converter for 'en-US' locale formats using non-numeric characters, e.g., 1000 formats to "1,000".

text.description: Use a mobile virtual keyboard for entering text.

oj-led-gauge.description: A LED gauge displays information graphically, highlighting a specific metric value in relation to its thresholds.
