oj-list-view.description: A list view displays data items as a list or a grid with highly interactive features.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: Specifies the alias for the current item when referenced inside the item template.

currentItem.description: Specifies the key of the item that should have keyboard focus. See the Help documentation for more information.

data.description: Specifies the data for the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

display.description: Specifies how the items should be displayed.

dnd.description: Customizes the drag and drop functionality. See the Help documentation for more information.

items.description: An object that describes drag functionality for a selected set of items. See the Help documentation for more information.

dataTypes.description: Specifies one or more MIME types to use for the dragged data in the dataTransfer object. See the Help documentation for more information.

drag.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drag" event as its argument.

dragEnd.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragend" event as its argument.

dragStart.description: A callback function that receives the "dragstart" event and context information as its arguments.

drop.description: Customizes the drop functionality.

items.description: An object that describes drop functionality for a selected set of items.

dataTypes.description: Specifies one or more data types that this component can accept. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as its arguments.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as its arguments.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as its arguments.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as its arguments.

items.description: Specify the item reordering functionality. See the Help documentation for more information.

disabled.description: Item reordering is disabled.

drillMode.description: Specifies whether expand or collapse operations are allowed.

collapsible.description: Group item can be expanded or collapsed by user.

none.description: The expand state of a group item cannot be changed by user.

expanded.description: Specifies the key set containing the keys of the items that should be expanded. See the Help documentation for more information.

firstSelectedItem.description: Specifies the key and data of the first selected item. See the Help documentation for more information.

gridlines.description: Customizes the functionality of how gridlines are shown in various parts of the list.

item.description: Specifies whether the grid lines should be visible.

visibleExceptLast.description: The horizontal gridlines are visible, except for the last item. Note this will not have an effect for themes that renders a bottom border for the component.

groupHeaderPosition.description: Specifies whether group header should stick to the top as user scrolls.

static.description: The group header position updates as user scrolls.

sticky.description: The group header is fixed at the top when user scrolls.

item.description: Customizes the functionality of each item on the list.

status.description: Not accessible by screen reader.

focusable.description: Specifies whether the item can receive keyboard focus. See the Help documentation for more information.

renderer.description: Specifies the renderer for the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

selectable.description: Specifies whether the item can be selected. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPolicy.description: Specifies how data are fetched as user scrolls down the list.

auto.description: The behavior is determined by the component. By default the behavior is the same as "loadMoreOnScroll" except when legacy TableDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "loadAll".

loadMoreOnScroll.description: Additional data is fetched when the user scrolls towards the bottom of the ListView.

scrollPolicyOptions.description: Specifies fetch options for scrolling behaviors that trigger data fetches. See the Help documentation for more information.

fetchSize.description: The number of items to fetch in each block

maxCount.description: The maximum total number of items to fetch

scroller.description: The element used to determine the scroll position as well as the maximum scroll position. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPosition.description: Specifies the current scroll position of the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

index.description: The zero-based index of the item. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

key.description: The key of the item. If DataProvider is used for data and the key does not exists in the DataProvider, then the value is ignored. If DataProvider is not used then ListView will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

offsetX.description: The horizontal offset in pixels relative to the item identified by key/index.

offsetY.description: The vertical offset in pixels relative to the item identified by key/index.

parent.description: The key of the parent where the index is relative to. If not specified, then the root is assumed

x.description: The horizontal position in pixels.

y.description: The vertical position in pixels.

scrollToKey.description: Specifies the behavior when ListView needs to scroll to a position based on an item key.

always.description: ListView will scroll to a position based on an item key as long as the key is valid.

auto.description: The behavior is determined by the component. By default the behavior is the same as "capability" except when legacy TableDataSource/TreeDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "always".

capability.description: ListView will only scroll to a position based on an item key if either the item has already been fetched or if the associated DataProvider supports 'immediate' iterationSpeed for 'fetchFirst' capability.

never.description: ListView will not change the scroll position if the request is based on an item key.

selected.description: Specifies the keys of the current selected items. See the Help documentation for more information.

status.description: Use selected attribute instead.

selection.description: Specifies the current selections in the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

selectionRequired.description: Specifies whether selection is required on the ListView.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

msgNoData.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by ListView when there are no items.

oj-menu.description: A menu displays a list of options in a popup.

disabled.description: Disables the menu if set to true.

openOptions.description: Specifies settings for launching a menu. See the Help documentation for more information.

display.description: Specifies whether the menu displays as a drop down or as a sheet. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Displays the menu as a sheet or drop down, depending on the screen width.

dropDown.description: Displays the menu as a drop down.

sheet.description: Displays the menu as a sheet.

initialFocus.description: Specifies focus behavior when the menu is initially opened.

firstItem.description: Focuses the first menu item (e.g. MenuButton DownArrow behavior).

menu.description: Focuses the menu itself, with no menu item focused (e.g. typical Context Menu behavior).

none.description: Leaves focus where it is, e.g. on the launching component. The application must verify that the result is accessible.

launcher.description: Specifies the DOM node that launches this menu. See the Help documentation for more information.

position.description: Specifies the position of a drop down menu when launched. See the Help documentation for more information.

at.description: Defines which position on the target element ("of") to align the positioned element against.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

vertical.description: Defines the vertical alignment of what the menu is aligned to. See the Help documentation for more information.

fit.description: shift the element away from the edge of the window.

flip.description: the element to the opposite side of the target and the collision detection is run again to see if it will fit. Whichever side allows more of the element to be visible will be used.

flipcenter.description: first applies the flip rule and follows with center alignment.

flipfit.description: first applies the flip logic, placing the element on whichever side allows more of the element to be visible. Then the fit logic is applied to ensure as much of the element is visible as possible.

none.description: no collision detection.

my.description: Defines which edge on the menu to align with the target ("of") element.

styleClasses.description: Inline messages will include a bottom border so that the messages section is demarcated from the contents below it. If this border is not desirable for certain page layouts, it can be removed by setting this marker class on oj-messages.

Inline messages (Banners) can be either Edge-to-Edge or Outlined. By default, the inline messages are rendered as Edge-to-Edge Banner messages. If Outlined Banner messages are preferred instead, add oj-messages-outlined class on the oj-messages element.

oj-picto-chart-item.name: oj-picto-chart-item
oj-picto-chart-item.description: The oj-picto-chart-item element is used to declare properties for picto chart items. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The border color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the item in pixels. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this picto chart item. This allows highlighting and filtering of items.

color.description: The color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

columnSpan.description: The number of columns each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a picto chart with mixed item sizes.

count.description: Specifies the number of times that the shape (or custom image) is drawn. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the item. Drillable items will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the item. Used for default tooltip and accessibility.

rowSpan.description: The number of rows each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a picto chart with mixed item sizes.

shape.description: The shape of the item. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

shortDesc.description: The description of the item. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-picto-chart.name: oj-picto-chart
oj-picto-chart.description: A picto chart displays information using icons to visualize an absolute number or the relative sizes of the different parts of a population.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation shown on initial display.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the itemTemplate slot.

columnCount.description: The number of columns in the picto chart. If unspecified, the number of columns will be automatically computed.

columnWidth.description: The width of a column in pixels. If unspecified, the column width will be automatically computed. See the Help documentation for more information.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the picto chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable objects will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Data items with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting data items.

items.description: An array of objects that define the picto chart items. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The border color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the item in pixels. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this item. If not specified, defaults to the item id or name. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with other visualization elements.

color.description: The color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

columnSpan.description: The number of columns each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a pictoChart with mixed item sizes.

count.description: Specifies the number of times that the shape (or custom image) is drawn. Fractional counts (such as 4.5) are supported; however, fractions other than the multiples of 0.5 should be avoided because the fractional rendering ignores the gaps between shapes and the irregularity of the shapes.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the item. Drillable items will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). To enable drilling for all items at once, use the drilling attribute in the top level.

id.description: The item id. The item id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used.

name.description: The name of the item. Used for default tooltip and accessibility.

rowSpan.description: The number of rows each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a pictoChart with mixed item sizes.

shape.description: The shape of the item. Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape. "None" will make the item transparent and can be used to create gaps. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

shortDesc.description: Short description string for accessibility users.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified with other properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the item color attribute. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified with other properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the item color attribute. Does not apply if custom image is specified. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

layout.description: Specifies the direction in which items are laid out.

layoutOrigin.description: Specifies where the first item is rendered. Subsequent items follow the first item according to the layout.

rowCount.description: The number of rows in the picto chart. If unspecified, the number of rows will be automatically computed.

rowHeight.description: The height of a row in pixels. If unspecified, the row height will be automatically computed. See the Help documentation for more information.

selection.description: An array of id strings, used to define the selected objects.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip. The function takes a context argument, provided by the picto chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleContainsControls.description: Used to describe a container that contains controls.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelClearSelection.description: Text shown for clearing multiple selection on touch devices.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

labelDataVisualization.description: Label for data visualizations used for accessibility.

labelInvalidData.description: Text shown when the component receives invalid data.

labelNoData.description: Text shown when the component receives no data.

stateCollapsed.description: Used to describe the collapsed state for accessibility.

stateDrillable.description: Used to describe a drillable object for accessibility.

stateExpanded.description: Used to describe the expanded state for accessibility.

stateHidden.description: Used to describe the hidden state for accessibility.

stateIsolated.description: Used to describe the isolated state for accessibility.

stateMaximized.description: Used to describe the maximized state for accessibility.

stateMinimized.description: Used to describe the minimized state for accessibility.

stateSelected.description: Used to describe the selected state for accessibility.

stateUnselected.description: Used to describe the unselected state for accessibility.

stateVisible.description: Used to describe the visible state for accessibility.

oj-popup.name: oj-popup

styleClasses.description: Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

styleClasses.description: Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-popup.description: A popup temporarily 'pops up' content in the foreground.

focusLoss.description: defines auto dismissal behavior when focus leaves the content of the popup or associated launcher. In addition, if what the popup is positioned to is not visible within an overflow area, the popup will auto close dismiss.

none.description: disables auto dismissal behaviors.

chrome.description: Specifies whether to use the border, shadow, and background colors from the active theme.

default.description: describes the popups border, shadow, and background color defined by the active theme.

none.description: turns off the outer chrome defined by the active theme.

initialFocus.description: Specifies whether the popup steals focus to its content when initially opened.

auto.description: is derived from the values of the modality and autoDismiss properties

firstFocusable.description: defines that a popup should grab focus to the first focusable element within the popup's content.

none.description: prevents the popup from stealing focus when open.

popup.description: focus to the root popup container (good choice for touch platforms).

modality.description: Specifies whether the popup should block user input to the page.

modal.description: The popup is modal. Interactions with other page elements are disabled. Modal popups overlay other page elements.

position.description: Specifies the position of a popup when launched. See the Help documentation for more information.

at.description: Defines which position on the target element ("of") to align the positioned element against.

horizontal.description: Defines the horizontal alignment of what the popup is aligned to.

end.description: evaluates to "right" in LTR mode and "left" in RTL mode.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

vertical.description: Defines the vertical alignment of what the popup is aligned to.

fit.description: shift the element away from the edge of the window.

flip.description: the element to the opposite side of the target and the collision detection is run again to see if it will fit. Whichever side allows more of the element to be visible will be used.

flipcenter.description: first applies the flip rule and follow with center alignment.

flipfit.description: first applies the flip logic, placing the element on whichever side allows more of the element to be visible. Then the fit logic is applied to ensure as much of the element is visible as possible.

none.description: no collision detection.

my.description: Defines which edge on the popup to align with the target ("of") element.

horizontal.description: Defines the horizontal alignment of the popup.

end.description: evaluates to "right" in LTR mode and "left" in RTL mode.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

vertical.description: Defines the vertical alignment of the popup.

of.description: Which element to position the popup against. See the Help documentation for more information.

offset.description: Defines a point offset in pixels from the ("my") alignment.

x.description: Horizontal alignment offset.

y.description: Vertical alignment offset.

tail.description: Specifies whether to display a decoration pointing from the popup to the launching element. See the Help documentation for more information.

none.description: no decoration will be displayed from the popup pointing to the launcher.

simple.description: enables showing the tail defined by the current theme.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

ariaCloseSkipLink.description: Label assigned to a hidden anchor tag used for accessibility navigation on platforms supporting VoiceOver. The link is injected as a sibling to the context area of an open popup and used for ojPopup#close activation.

ariaFocusSkipLink.description: Label assigned to a hidden anchor tag used for accessibility navigation on platforms supporting VoiceOver. The link is injected as a sibling to the launcher of an open popup. The launcher is passed as the first argument to ojPopup#open. Activation of the link will move focus to the content of the associated popup.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusFirstFocusable.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on desktop platforms when a popup opens and steals initial focus.
Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on platforms supporting VoiceOver when a popup opens and steals initial focus.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusNone.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on desktop platforms when a popup opens but doesn't change focus.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusNoneTouch.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on platforms supporting VoiceOver when a popup opens but doesn't change focus.

close.description: Closes the popup.

describedBy.description: The form component's oj-label automatically sets described-by to make it accessible. It is not meant to be set by application developer.

disabled.description: Specifies if the component is disabled. If true, then all of its inputs and labels are also disabled. See the Help documentation for more information.

displayOptions.description: Display options for auxiliary content that determines whether or not it should be displayed.

instruction.description: Represents advisory information for the component, such as would be appropriate for a tooltip.

definition.description: Hint for help definition text associated with the label.

source.description: Help source URL associated with the component.

labelEdge.description: Defines how the label of a component is created. See the Help documentation for more information.

inside.description: The component creates the label using the label-hint attribute.

none.description: The component will not have a label, regardless of whether it's in an oj-form-layout or not.

provided.description: Label is provided by the parent if the parent is an oj-form-layout.

labelHint.description: Represents a hint for oj-form-layout element to render a label on the editable component.

labelledBy.description: Establishes a relationship between this component and another element, typically an oj-label custom element. See the Help documentation for more information.

messagesCustom.description: A list of messages added by an application to the component. See the Help documentation for more information.

optionRenderer.description: The renderer function that renders the content of each option.

options.description: The option items for the Radioset.

optionsKeys.description: Specify the key names to use in the options array. Depending on options-keys means that the signature of the data does not match what is supported by the options attribute.

label.description: The key name for the label.

value.description: The key name for the value.

readonly.description: Specifies whether the component is read-only. A read-only element cannot be modified, but user interaction is allowed. See the Help documentation for more information.

required.description: Specifies whether the component is required or optional. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

readonlyNoValue.description: Used for the readonly radioset when no option is selected.

required.description: Provides properties to customize the summary, detail and hint text used by the implicit required validator associated to any editable component that supports the required option.

hint.description: Hint text used by required validation error.

messageDetail.description: Message text that describes the details of the required validation error.

status.description: This is deprecated because in the Redwood design system form components do not show validator summaries, so this is no longer needed.

messageSummary.description: Message text for summarizing a required validation error.

userAssistanceDensity.description: Specifies the density of the form component's user assistance presentation.

compact.description: Messages, help, hints, and required will not be shown inline; they will show in a mode that keeps the screen more compact, like a popup for the messages, and a required icon to indicate Required.

efficient.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with reserved space.

reflow.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with no reserved space.

valid.description: The validity state of the component

invalidHidden.description: The component has invalid messages hidden and no invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

invalidShown.description: The component has invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

pending.description: The component is waiting for the validation state to be determined. The "pending" state is set at the start of the convert/validate process.

valid.description: The component is valid

value.description: The value of the component. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-sunburst.name: oj-sunburst
oj-sunburst.description:
A sunburst is an interactive data visualization in which hierarchical data is represented in concentric rings.
Each ring segment is proportionally sized relative to the other segments at a given level.

animationDuration.description: Specifies the animation duration in milliseconds. For data change animations with multiple stages, the value specifies the duration of each stage.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend and other visualization elements. The categories array of each node is required to be a superset of the categories array of its parent node. If not specified, the ids of the node and its ancestors will be used.

The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

oj-tab-bar.description: A tab bar allows navigation between different content sections.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

display.description: Specifies what needs to be displayed. See the Help documentation for more information.

all.description: Display both the label and icons.

edge.description: Specifies the edge position of the Tab Bar.

bottom.description: This renders list items horizontally. Generally used when tab bar placed on bottom of content section.

end.description: This renders list items vertically. Generally used when tab bar placed on right/end of content section.

start.description: This renders list items vertically. Generally used when tab bar placed on left/start of content section.

top.description: This renders list items horizontally. Generally used when tab bar placed on top of content section.

item.description: Customize the functionality of each tab on Tab Bar.

renderer.description: Specifies the renderer for the tab item. See the Help documentation for more information.

selectable.description: Specifies whether the tab can be selected. See the Help documentation for more information.

layout.description: Specifies whether to stretch the tab bar items to occupy available space or to condense items.

overflow.description: Specifies overflow behaviour for the Tab Bar.

hidden.description: Overflow is clipped, and the rest of the content will be invisible.

popup.description: Popup menu will be shown with overflowed items.

reorderable.description: Specifies whether tabs can be reordered.

disabled.description: Disables reordering of items in tabbar.

enabled.description: Enables reordering of items in tabbar.

selection.description: Specifies the key of the selected item. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleReorderAfterItem.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when the tentative drop target is after a certain item.

accessibleReorderBeforeItem.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when the tentative drop target is before a certain item.

accessibleReorderTouchInstructionText.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader touch instructional text for reordering items.

labelCut.description: Provides properties to customize the context menu cut label.

labelPasteAfter.description: Provides properties to customize the context menu paste after label.

labelPasteBefore.description: Provides properties to customize the context menu paste before label.

labelRemove.description: Provides properties to customize the context menu remove label.

msgFetchingData.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by Tab Bar when waiting for data.

msgNoData.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by Tab Bar when there are no items.

removeCueText.description: Text cue for the removable tab, used as the aria-label for the close icon.

selectedLabel.description: Provides text to read to screen reader when an item is selected.

truncation.description: Specifies whether truncation needs to be applied.

none.description: tabs always take up the space needed by the title texts.

progressive.description: If not enough space is available to display all of the tabs, then the width of each tab title is restricted just enough to allow all tabs to fit. All tab titles that are truncated are displayed with ellipses. However the width of each tab title will not be truncated below $tabBarTruncatedLabelMinWidth.

editMode.description: Specifies if the table is read-only or editable. See the Help documentation for more information.

none.description: The table is read-only and is a single Tab stop.

rowEdit.description: The table has single row at a time editability and the cells within the editable row are tabbable.

editRow.description: Specifies the row that is currently being edited. See the Help documentation for more information.

firstSelectedRow.description: Read-only property used for retrieving the key and data of the first selected row. See the Help documentation for more information.

data.description: The data for first selected row.

key.description: The key of first selected row.

horizontalGridVisible.description: Specifies the visibility of the horizontal gridlines. See the Help documentation for more information.

auto.description: Determined by display attribute.

disabled.description: Horizontal gridlines are disabled.

layout.description: The column sizing method used for the Table and its columns.

contents.description: When specified, the default column sizing is determined by the contents of the data. Does not require an overall width set on the Table. Can have performance issues when large numbers of columns and/or rows are initially rendered.

fixed.description: When specified, the default column sizing is determined by column weights. Requires an overall width set on the Table (width='100%', width='200rem', etc.) Very performant when rendering large numbers of columns and/or rows.

row.description: Customizes the functionality of each row in the table.

editable.description: Specifies whether the row can be edited. See the Help documentation for more information.

selectable.description: Specifies whether the row can be selected. See the Help documentation for more information.

sticky.description: Specifies whether the row is sticky. See the Help documentation for more information.

rowRenderer.description: A function that returns row content. The function takes a context argument, provided by the table. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPolicy.description: Specifies how data are fetched as user scrolls down the table.

auto.description: Determined by element. The default is to have the same behavior as "loadMoreOnScroll" except when legacy TableDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "loadAll".

loadMoreOnScroll.description: Additional data are fetched when the user scrolls to the bottom of the table. This option should be used only when table height is specified.

scrollPolicyOptions.description: Specifies fetch options for scrolling behaviors that trigger data fetches.

fetchSize.description: The number of data rows to fetch in each block.

maxCount.description: The maximum number of rows to display before fetching more data rows will be stopped.

scroller.description: The CSS selector string to an element used to determine the scroll position as well as the maximum scroll position. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollerOffsetBottom.description: The bottom offset value (in pixels) used for the Table's external scroller. This value is used to specify the location where the Table's footer region becomes 'sticky' when the 'scroller' attribute is specified.

scrollerOffsetEnd.description: The end offset value (in pixels) used for the Table's external scroller. This value is used to specify the location where the Table's frozen 'end' columns (or frozen 'start' columns in RTL) become 'sticky' when the 'scroller' attribute is specified.

scrollerOffsetStart.description: The start offset value (in pixels) used for the Table's external scroller. This value is used to specify the location where the Table's frozen 'start' columns (or frozen 'end' columns in RTL) become 'sticky' when the 'scroller' attribute is specified.

scrollerOffsetTop.description: The top offset value (in pixels) used for the Table's external scroller. This value is used to specify the location where the Table's header region becomes 'sticky' when the 'scroller' attribute is specified.

scrollPosition.description: Specifies the scroll position of the table. See the Help documentation for more information.

columnIndex.description: The zero-based index of the cell at the origin of the table.

columnKey.description: The key of the column. This corresponds to the identifier of the column specified in columns. If the column does not exists then the value is ignored.

offsetX.description: The horizontal offset in pixels relative to the column identified by columnKey/columnIndex.

offsetY.description: The vertical offset in pixels relative to the row identified by rowKey/rowIndex.

rowIndex.description: The zero-based index of the cell at the origin of the table. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll and the row index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the table is reached and there are no more rows to fetch.

rowKey.description: The key of the row. If DataProvider is used for data and the key does not exists in the DataProvider, then the value is ignored. If DataProvider is not used then Table will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the table is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

x.description: The horizontal position in pixels.

y.description: The vertical position in pixels.

scrollToKey.description: Specifies the behavior when Table needs to scroll to a position based on an item key.

always.description: Table will scroll to a position based on a row key as long as the key is valid.

auto.description: The behavior is determined by the component. By default the behavior is the same as "capability" except when legacy TableDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "always".

capability.description: Table will only scroll to a position based on a row key if either the row has already been fetched or if the associated DataProvider supports 'immediate' iterationSpeed for 'fetchFirst' capability.

never.description: Table will not change the scroll position if the request is based on a row key.

oj-tag-cloud-item.description: The oj-tag-cloud-item element is used to declare properties for tag cloud items. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-tag-cloud.name: oj-tag-cloud
oj-tag-cloud.description: A tag cloud is an interactive data visualization of textual data, where the importance of each tagged word or phrase is represented by font size or color.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

items.description: An array of objects defining the data items for the tag cloud items. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

id.description: The item id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the DataProvider case.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the item text.

oj-thematic-map.name: oj-thematic-map
oj-thematic-map.description:
A thematic map is an interactive data visualization that displays data corresponding to geographic locations or regions.
             Applications are required to supply a mapProvider for a valid thematic map.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds. See the Help documentation for more information.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

areaData.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the areas of the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

areas.description: An array of objects that define area data layers. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this area. This allows highlighting and filtering of areas.

color.description: The area color.

id.description: The identifier for this area. The id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the case.

label.description: Text used for the area's label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style defining the label style for this area. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a Feature provided in the mapProvider geo object that this area is associated with.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the area will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The description of this element. Will be lazily created if a function is used. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the area.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the area. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the areaTemplate, markerTemplate, or linkTemplate slots.

focusRenderer.description: An optional callback function to update the data item in response to changes in keyboard focus state. The function takes a context argument, provided by the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Data items matching categories in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

hoverRenderer.description: An optional callback function to update the node in response to changes in hover state. The function takes a context argument, provided by the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

initialZooming.description: Specifies whether the map will zoom to fit the data objects on initial render.

isolatedItem.description: The id for the isolated area of this area data layer. If set, only the isolated area will be displayed.

labelDisplay.description: Specifies how labels for this layer should be displayed.

auto.description: Renders the label if it fits within the area bounds.

labelType.description: Specifies which type of map labels to display.

linkData.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the links of the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

links.description: An array of objects that define the map links. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this link. This allows highlighting and filtering of links.

color.description: The link color.

endLocation.description: An object used to determine the end point of the link.

id.description: The marker or area id to be used as the end point.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a Feature provided in the mapProvider geo object to be used as the end point.

x.description: The x coordinate which can represent latitude of the end point.

y.description: The y coordinate which can represent longitude of the end point.

id.description: The identifier for this link. The id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the case.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the link will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The description of this element. Will be lazily created if a function is used. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

startLocation.description: An object used to determine the start point of the link.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a Feature provided in the mapProvider geo object to be used as the start point.

geo.description: An object defining a custom area's coordinates and "properties" object. See the Help documentation for more information.

propertiesKeys.description: An object specifying "properties" object keys to use for custom area id and label mappings.

id.description: The required name of the "properties" key to use as the location id that will map a data item to a map area.

longLabel.description: The optional name of the "properties" key to use for rendering area labels when labelType is set to "long".

shortLabel.description: The optional name of the "properties" key to use for rendering area labels when labelType is set to "short".

oj-timeline-item.description: The oj-timeline-item element is used to declare properties for timeline items. See the Help documentation for more information.

background.description: The background color of the item bubble. If the item is of type "duration-event", then a color stripe will also be rendered in the item bubble. The exact background and stripe color values come from the CSS and vary based on theme. For each item, there is an accessibility requirement for use cases where a color difference is used to convey information. The application is responsible for making sure that the information conveyed is also available in visible text.

blue.description: Blue background (and blue color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

green.description: Green background (and green color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

orange.description: Orange background (and orange color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

purple.description: Purple background (and purple color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

red.description: Red background (and red color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

teal.description: Teal background (and teal color stripe for "duration-event" type item).

viewportNavigationMode.description: The viewport navigation mode of the timeline.

continuous.description: In continuous mode, users can pan horizontally and vertically, and zoom in and out throughout the entire timeline.

discrete.description: In discrete mode only vertical panning is supported. Zooming is not supported. The viewport will use the viewport-start and the viewport-end to set the viewport duration width. Discrete mode will show "preview wings" which will extend slightly beyond the start and end of your actual viewport-start and viewport-end dates. The user can navigate the timeline via paging arrows, which may be disabled if the timeline does not have a full viewport worth of time data to display. To get the best usage, the timeline start and end should be set with a small buffer before and after their actual values (e.g. Dec 15, 2012 - Jan 15, 2014) The viewport-start and viewport-end should be carefully configured to start and end within the time period of usage. The timeline will pick the closest axis label when navigating through with the navigation arrows. Note: discrete mode is only supported in redwood. In vertical timeline orientation, the viewport navigation mode uses continuous behavior.

oj-treemap.description: A tree map is an interactive data visualization in which hierarchical data is represented across two dimensions by the size and color of nested rectangular nodes.

animationDuration.description: Specifies the animation duration in milliseconds. For data change animations with multiple stages, the value specifies the duration of each stage.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

animationUpdateColor.description: Specifies the color displayed during a data change animation when a node is updated.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the nodeTemplate slot.

colorLabel.description: Specifies the label displayed in the legend describing the color metric of the treemap.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the treemap. See the Help documentation for more information.

exceptionStatus.description: Data sets from a DataProvider cannot be sent to WebDriverJS; use ViewModels or page variables instead.

displayLevels.description: The number of levels of nodes to display. By default all nodes are displayed.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable nodes will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire ojBeforeDrill and ojDrill events on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

groupGaps.description: Specifies whether gaps are displayed between groups. Gaps can be useful for drawing attention to the differences between groups.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Nodes with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightMode.description: Specifies whether the highlight-mode should be by category or descendants.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Nodes matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over the nodes.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting nodes.

isolatedNode.description: The id of the initially isolated node.

layout.description: Specifies the layout of the treemap. See the Help documentation for more information.

nodeContent.description: An object defining custom node content for the treemap. Only leaf nodes with no child nodes will have the custom content rendered.

renderer.description: A function that returns custom node content. The function takes a context argument, provided by the treemap. See the Help documentation for more information.

nodeDefaults.description: An object defining default properties for the nodes. See the Help documentation for more information.

groupLabelDisplay.description: The label display behavior for group nodes.

nodes.description: An array of objects defining the data for the nodes. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend and other visualization elements. The categories array of each node is required to be a superset of the categories array of its parent node. If not specified, the ids of the node and its ancestors will be used.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled for the node. Drillable nodes will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). To enable drilling for all nodes at once, use the drilling attribute in the top level.

groupLabelDisplay.description: The label display behavior for group nodes.

header.description: An object defining the properties for the node header.

isolate.description: Specifies whether isolate behavior is enabled on the node.

labelHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the header title.

useNodeColor.description: Specifies whether the node color should be displayed in the header.

id.description: The id of the node. For the DataProvider case, the key for the node will be used as the id.

oj-validation-group.name: oj-validation-group
oj-validation-group.description: A validation group tracks and summarizes the current validity state of a group of components.

valid.description: Read-only property used for retrieving the current validity state of the group of components being tracked. See the Help documentation for more information.

invalidHidden.description: The component has invalid messages hidden and no invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

invalidShown.description: The component has invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

pending.description: The component is waiting for the validation state to be determined.

valid.description: The component is valid

focusOn.description: Sets the focus on one of the enabled components that is being tracked. See the Help documentation for more information.

params.name: key
params.description: "@firstInvalidShown" will focus on first invalidShown enabled component in DOM order, if any. When no parameter is passed in, the method will focus on first enabled component regardless of the valid state, if any. An enabled component is one that is not disabled or readonly.

getProperty.description: Retrieves a value for a property or a single subproperty for complex properties.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

setProperties.description: Performs a batch set of properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

setProperty.description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to set. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.name: value
params.description: The new value to set the property to.

showMessages.description: Takes all deferred messages and shows them on each enabled component. An enabled component is one that is not disabled or readonly. As a result, the valid property may be updated; e.g., if the valid state was "invalidHidden" before showMessages(), the valid state will become "invalidShown" after showMessages().

slots.description: The <oj-validation-group> accepts any DOM elements in its Default slot but only tracks the validity state of any JET custom element descendents that contain the valid property.

styleClasses.name: oj-label-for-non-control
styleClasses.displayName: oj-label Styling for non-JET Form Controls
styleClasses.description: Place on a label element along with oj-label-nocomp when you want to style it like a JET oj-label but the label isn't associated with a JET form control, such as when you have a label for some plain text.

status.description: This class is not supported in the Redwood nor the Alta theme, and will be removed from the JET API in a future release. Use a JET oj-label component with its label-id attribute instead.

styleClasses.name: oj-label-inline
styleClasses.description: Place on a label element along with oj-label-nocomp to inline the label with the sibling DOM element when you don't want to use the responsive design classes (e.g., oj-md-labels-inline).

status.description: This class is not supported in the Redwood theme, and will be removed from the JET API in a future release. Use a JET oj-label-value with label-edge='start' instead.

styleClasses.name: oj-label-inline-top
styleClasses.description: Place on a label element along with oj-label-nocomp and oj-label-inline selectors to inline the label with the sibling DOM element and have zero margin-top.

status.description: This class is not supported in the Redwood theme, and will be removed from the JET API in a future release. Use a JET oj-label-value with label-edge='start' instead.

styleClasses.name: oj-label-nocomp
styleClasses.description: Place on a label element when it isn't a JET component but you want it to be styled like a JET oj-label.

status.description: This class is not supported in the Redwood theme, and will be removed from the JET API in a future release. Use a JET oj-label component with its label-id attribute instead.

styleClasses.name: oj-label-nowrap
styleClasses.description: Place on a label element along with oj-label-nocomp to have it not wrap when you don't want to use the responsive design classes (e.g., oj-md-labels-nowrap or oj-md-label-nowrap).
